			<c01 level="item">
				<did>
					<unitid>Bd. Ms. Msst I 7003</unitid>
					<unittitle>Two copies of a typescript titled The German Element in the United
						States with special reference to its political, moral, social, and
						educational influence by Albert Bernhardt Faust. Offered in competition for
						the Conrad Seipp memorial price, March 22, 1907. Each copy is in two parts
						in bound volumes. Part two gives the subtitle as: with reference to the
						agricultural and industrial development of the country; with reference to
						politics, education, culture, social ad ethical standards. The two copies
						differ slightly. Both copies have some hand written notes, corrections, and
						marginalia. </unittitle>
